               <bioghist altrender="Biographical Information" encodinganalog="545"><head>Biographical Information:</head>
                              <p>Born about 1811 in Surrey, England, John Chatfield was a sailor who jumped ship in New York harbor in 1841 and made his way westward to Illinois. One of DeKalb County&#039;s first settlers, Chatfield became a wealthy farmer and land owner, and Republican party member. He died in 1890</p>
                           </bioghist>
         

